@node "INFO" "SN LoginConfig v3.3 - Information"
@toc "MAIN"
┌───────────────────────────────────┐
  SN LoginConfig v3.3 - Information
└───────────────────────────────────┘

   Ever have users complain that the sys.welcome is too long or contains
stuff they have no interest in?  I thought so, so I wrote this to fix all
that!  Now you can choose what users MUST go through during login and the
users can choose to either see or skip the rest!
   I have attempted to include everything this type of program needs, but
mine being the only SysOp's viewpoint, I have almost certainly left out a
certain feature someone wants or needs.  Please let me know of these and I
will do all I can to add this into the next release.

Features to note:
  - Multi-line compatible.  You don't have to worry about conflictions.
    Everyone has their own configuration!
  - Provides the following pre-login features:  Mail Check, Offline
    Mail Reader (OMR) .QWK packet grab, .QWK packet upload and OMR Grab/
    .QWK upload combo.
  - Replaces sys.welcome with included sys.welcome and you never have
    to modify your sys.welcome again.
  - Self-cleaning.  Leaves no temp files lying around.
  - First time users log on after installation) get the default
    configuration first and then automatically choose their new config.
  - Long distance users have their own login sequence (_LDSpeed).
    It contains less unuseful items to speed up their login.
  - Higher access users (level is SysOp changeable) can opt to use a
    shorter sequence (_HiSpeed) every time they log on or use their
    normal one.
  - New users have a very short sequence (_NewUser) giving them
    restricted access to things until they are validated.

───SN/AHI (910) 326-3804 (28.8k)─────────────────────────────────────────
@endnode
@node "HISTORY" "SN LoginConfig v3.3 - History"
@toc "MAIN"
┌───────────────────────────────┐
  SN LoginConfig v3.3 - History
└───────────────────────────────┘

  v3.3 - Changed the way the _Begin, _Added and _End files interact
         eliminating the need to reset users' configs when the
         _Begin or _End files change.  Only changing the _Added file
         makes resetting necessary.  Also, made the files self-aware.
         Removed the path variables in the config sections.  Combined
         LC and LCR into just LC.
  v3.2 - Obliterated level-switching bug by removing the need for it!
         Almost completely rewrote the program to be safer and more
         efficient.  All features work as stated, no adverse affects
         noted.
  v3.1 - Beta-release.  Working out level-switching bug, adding no show
         first routine and replacing MailCheck with more efficient method.
         Had to temporarily disable the [B]oth option.
  v3.0 - Finally worked out all the kinks with the new features.  This
         official release includes MailCheck, OMR-Grab, .QWK Upload and
         OMR-Grab/.QWK Upload combo.  Everything should be running
         smoothly now.
  v2.9 - Various bugfixes and beta releases heading towards v3.0.
    |    
  v2.4   
  v2.3 - Bugs fixed and the program streamlined to work better and faster.
         Also added LDSpeed login, HiSpeed login and NewUser login sequences.
  v2.2 - If _Config.End or _Config.Begin is not present (i.e. you do not
         need one or the other or both) it won't die on you now.  Now you
         supply the full descriptive question for each addable entry.  No
         more "See whatever?", it says exactly what you tell it to.
  v2.1 - Restructured to work more efficiently.  Now, the sys.welcome file
         stays the same and a tmp file in RAM: is executed.  If the user
         doesn't have a config, a full sys.welcome is copied to their dir
         and executed, then the config program is run so the users can
         choose what they want next login.
  v2.0 - 2nd generation pre-release.  First revamping of routines.
  v1.0 - 1st generation.  Rudimentary, but operational.

───SN/AHI (910) 326-3804 (28.8k)─────────────────────────────────────────
@endnode
